 to power this orion.<br>
2. We will make the ammonium nitrate by mixing fertilizer<br>
(potassium nitrate) with gasoline inside of cylindrical metal<br>
fuel barrels. This was the procedure used to make the depth<br>
charges used by  our destroyers to kill Nazi U-boats during world war 2.*<br>
3. This orion will have a 10 meter diameter steel plate on its tail.<br>
4. The explosive charges will be dropped through a hole in the center of it.<br>
5. Each charge will have a lever that will be moved up when it is dropped through the hole. This will start a 1 second time fuze.<br>
6. The barrel shaped pulse unit will store 1600 pounds of high<br>
 explosive inside of it (NH3 NO3.)The barrel will be made of steel and will serve as a high explosive lense to direct the entire shock wave of the explosion upward at the inertial<br>
 plate. The lid on the barrel will be made of aluminium.<br>
The way it works is like in a modern bullet. When the powder explodes the cartridge shell will direct its force at the bullet to fire it.<br>
7. The debris velocity will be in the range 6000 to 7000 meters per second.<br>
8. The pulse unit will drop 10 meters below the plate in one second and it will explode. There will be 1 pulse unit per second detonated<br>
.<br>
9. The basic design will be similar to that of put put<br>
in 1963, but there will be many more pulse units.<br>
10. 1600 pounds * 20,000 feet per second = 3,200,000<br>
pounds of thrust.The machine will stand on 10 meter<br>
steel legs,around the pusher plate,in a pyramid geometry.<br>
It could be up to 60-70 meters in height.<br>
11. This orion will have a mass ratio of 5 /1.<br>
12. Its weight will be 2,500,000 pounds at take off.<br>
13. There will be 1000 1 ton charges like those described above in the magizine.<br>
14. Burn time for this orion is 1000 seconds.<br>
This is 16 minutes and 40 seconds.<br>
15.It will achieve an average acceleration of 1.28 G s<br>
which is 12.8 m/sec upward.<br>
16. V = Ve * ln/mi/mf <br>
v= 20,000 ft/sec * ln 5/1 which is about 32 189 ft/sec.<br>
This 6.096 miles/sec which is 22,069 miles per hour.<br>
17. This orion will burn until it gets 9000 m/sec, in velocity<br>
 and it will use the remaining  pu s for de-orbiting it self<br>
  after that.<br>
 18.After orion is burned out it will be detached, and only the payload will be used after that. <br>
